# VCF Migration Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and configure as needed

# =============================================================================
# PRICING OPTIONS (Choose one)
# =============================================================================

# Option 1: Cloud Functions Proxy (RECOMMENDED)
# Deploy the pricing proxy to IBM Cloud Functions and set the URL here.
# This keeps your API key secure on the server side.
# See: functions/pricing-proxy/README.md for deployment instructions
VITE_PRICING_PROXY_URL=https://us-south.functions.cloud.ibm.com/api/v1/web/your-namespace/default/vcf-pricing-proxy

# Option 2: Direct API Key (NOT RECOMMENDED for production)
# If you don't want to use the proxy, you can set the API key directly.
# WARNING: This exposes your API key in the browser!
# Get your API key from: https://cloud.ibm.com/iam/apikeys
# VITE_IBM_CLOUD_API_KEY=your-api-key-here

# =============================================================================
# PROFILES API
# =============================================================================
# The IBM Cloud API key is also used to fetch live VPC instance profiles,
# bare metal profiles, and ROKS flavors from IBM Cloud APIs:
#
# - VPC VSI Profiles: GET /v1/instance/profiles
# - VPC Bare Metal:   GET /v1/bare_metal_server/profiles
# - ROKS Flavors:     GET /global/v2/getFlavors
#
# If no API key is set, the app uses static profile data from ibmCloudConfig.json
#
# ROKS-Supported Bare Metal Profiles (with NVMe for ODF):
# - bx2d.metal.96x384: 48 cores, 384 GiB, 8×3200GB NVMe
# - cx2d.metal.96x192: 48 cores, 192 GiB, 8×3200GB NVMe
# - mx2d.metal.96x768: 48 cores, 768 GiB, 8×3200GB NVMe
#
# REQUIRED IAM PERMISSIONS for Service ID:
# -----------------------------------------
# To use the live profiles API, the Service ID associated with the API key
# must have the following IAM access policies:
#
# 1. VPC Infrastructure Services
#    - Service: VPC Infrastructure Services
#    - Resources: All resources (or specific region)
#    - Role: Viewer (minimum)
#
# 2. Kubernetes Service (optional, for ROKS machine types)
#    - Service: Kubernetes Service
#    - Resources: All resources
#    - Role: Viewer
#
# To add these permissions:
# 1. Go to https://cloud.ibm.com/iam/serviceids
# 2. Select your Service ID
# 3. Click "Access" tab
# 4. Click "Assign access"
# 5. Select the services above and assign Viewer role

# =============================================================================
# NOTES
# =============================================================================
# - If neither is set, the app will use static fallback pricing and profile data
# - The proxy is preferred for pricing because it:
#   1. Keeps credentials server-side (secure)
#   2. Caches responses to reduce API calls
#   3. Handles CORS issues automatically
#   4. Falls back gracefully if API is unavailable
